Diaper rash can make even the happiest of babies irritable and put them in pain. Ensure that your bundle of joy doesn’t turn grumpy with this rash cream from Himalaya.

Five-leaved Chaste Tree Extract

This cream has the extract of the chaste tree that has anti-inflammatory properties that soothes the rash and inhibits microbe growth as well.

Natural Zinc

The zinc content in this diaper rash cream from Himalaya cools down the inflamed skin and dries moisture up quickly to ensure that the rash clears quickly.

Aloe Vera and Almond Oil

column16:
'desc': [u'

Himalaya Baby Powder (400 g) Price: Rs.125

Key Features

  • Controlling the Body Odour
  • Sandalwood Extract Cools and Olive Oil Nourishes the Baby's Tender Skin
  • Relieving Itching on the Baby's Tender Skin
  • Helps in Excess Sweating
  • Has Antiseptic Properties and Accelerates Healing

Taking care of your newborn’s skin can seem difficult and challenging as they have very fragile skin. Himalaya Baby Powder has been formulated specially to soothe the baby’s skin from excessive sweating and unwanted itching. Sweat and dust trapped in the skin due to disproportionate sweating can cause allergies and skin infections. This can be avoided and prevented by using the Himalaya Baby Powder. Replete with ingredients like natural zinc and olive oil this Baby Powder from Himalaya safeguards your tiny tot’s skin from prickly heat and unwanted sweating.

Natural zinc has antiseptic properties that accelerate healing of the tender skin on your little darling’s body. Khus Khus is an antiperspirant that checks the amount of sweat produced and comforts the skin with the astringent properties. In addition to this the almond oil infused in the Himalaya Baby Powder helps in restoring the moisture to your little one’s skin.

You can sprinkle this Himalaya Baby Powder all over your infant’s skin liberally and this will keep your baby’s skin free of prickly heat rashes as well. This Baby Powder can also be used during nappy change to absorb any excess moisture and also before bedtime so that the baby has a peaceful sleep.

']
